But there are some setbacks. Issues: Inability to press more then 1 button for example, (a+d, or space+x) hold this app back. Playback is slow, kinda sluggish making some swf games respond late. Need auto frame rate skip. Purchased this app in hope that the developer will improve its performance. Kyocera Hydro 4.0.4(rooted)

Excellent performance, functionality, & usability. Ability to play local swf files just about completes my Honeycomb's (Asus TF101) "play any video" repertoire. I've only just had this app 1 day and used it 5 or 6 times, but the detailed settings and features make this seem a mature product. The user interface is very low tech, almost text based. English is not polished but don't be put off. Make sure you have latest FlashPlayer, & go full-screen via flash's "tap, long-tap" function to solve display probs.
